cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as salient object segmentation, edge detection, and skeleton extraction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a unified architecture for solving these tasks, which involves deep learning techniques. This suggests that the paper could also belong to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of hierarchical features, which could fall under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on multiple datasets, which could also place it under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
